{"parse":{"title":"hey","pageid":23501,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Hey}}\n==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|hā}}, {{IPA|en|/heɪ/}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Pvanp7-hey.wav|a=UK}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-hey.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{audio|en|EN-AU ck1 hey.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{rhymes|en|eɪ|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|en|hay|;|hae<aa:pane-pain>}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|hey}}, {{m|enm|hei}}, also without ''h-'' in {{m|enm|ey}}, from {{inh|en|ang|*hē}}, {{m|ang|ēa|pos=interjection}}, attested as first element in {{m|ang|hēlā}}, {{m|ang|ēalā|t=O!, alas!, oh!, lo!}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|hé}}, {{m|nl|hei|t=hi, hey}}, {{cog|de|hei|t=hey, wow}}, {{cog|da|-}} and {{cog|sv|hej|t=hello, hey}}, {{cog|fo|hey|t=hey, hello}}, {{cog|non|-}}, {{cog|is|-}} and {{cog|no|hei|t=hey}}, {{cog|pl|hej|t=hey, hello|}}, {{cog|ro|hei}}, {{cog|ru|эй|t=hey}}; see {{l|en|heigh}}. Probably a natural expression, as may be inferred from its presence with similar meaning in many other unrelated languages: for example, {{cog|my|ဟေး}}, {{cog|fi|hei}}, Unami ''hè'', and {{cog|cmn|哎|tr=āi}}, and various sound-alikes as {{cog|grc|εἶα}} and {{cog|la|eia}}, {{m|la|eho}}, {{cog|sa|हे}}. See also {{l|en|hello}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|hay}}\n* {{l|en|heigh}}\n\n====Interjection====\n{{en-intj}} {{tlb|en|informal}}\n\n# An [[exclamation]] to get [[attention]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey''', look at this!}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey'''! Listen!}}\n# A [[protest]] or [[reprimand]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey'''! Stop that!}}\n# An [[expression]] of [[surprise]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey'''! This is new!}}\n# {{n-g|An [[informal]] [[greeting]], similar to {{m|en|hi}}.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey'''! How's it going?}}\n# A [[request]] for [[repetition]] or [[explanation]]; an expression of [[confusion]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hey'''? [[how's that|How's that]]?}}\n# {{n-g|Used as a [[tag question]], to emphasise what goes before or to request that the listener express an opinion about what has been said.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1900|author=w:Joseph Conrad|title=w:Lord Jim|page=vi. 54 |passage=\"Who 's a cur - now - '''hey'''?\"}}\n# A meaningless [[beat]] [[marker]] or extra, [[filler]] [[syllable]] in song lyrics.\n#: {{ux|en|The chorus is \"nana na na, nana na na '''hey hey hey''', goodbye\".}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|exclamation to get attention}} {{l|en|oi}}, {{l|en|yo}}; see also [[Thesaurus:hey]]\n* {{sense|expression of surprise}} {{l|en|blimey}}, {{l|en|gee whiz}}, {{l|en|yowzah}}; see also [[Thesaurus:wow]]\n* {{sense|for repetition or explanation}} {{l|en|eh}}, {{l|en|huh}}\n* {{sense|informal greeting}} {{l|en|hi}}, {{l|en|howdy}}, {{l|en|wotcher}}; see also [[Thesaurus:hello]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|but hey\n|heyday\n|hey hey\n|hey ho\n|hey Joe\n|heyo\n|hey pass\n|hey presto\n|hey Rube\n|hey rube|hey mister\n|hey there\n|hey up\n|hey ya\n|like hey-go-mad\n|stomp clap hey\n|what the hey\n|yehey\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|exclamation to get attention}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|يَاه}}, {{t|ar|اسمع}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|بقولك ايه}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|هيه|tr=hē}}, {{t|acw|ياهو|tr=yāhō}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|հեյ}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|гэй}}, {{t|be|эй}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|хей}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ep}}, {{t+|ca|ei}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|喂|tr=wai3}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|喂|tr=wèi}}, {{t+|cmn|哎|tr=āi}}, {{t+|cmn|嗨|tr=hāi}}, {{t+|cmn|嘿|tr=hēi}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|hele}}, {{t+|cs|hej}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hallo}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hé}}, {{t-check|nl|[[hé]] [[daar]]}} <!-- was \"he daar\" - assumed sum-of-parts; if an idiom, remove the wikilinks to the individual words. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|he}}, {{t+|eo|hej}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|hei}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|hei}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|hé}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|oi}}, {{t+|gl|ei}}, {{t+|gl|eh}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Hallo}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|οὗτος|m}}, {{t|grc|αὕτη|f}}, {{t|grc|ἄγε|s}}, {{t|grc|ἄγετε|p}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|अरे}}, {{t+|hi|अजी}}, {{t+|hi|हे}}, {{t+|hi|रे}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hé}}, {{t+|hu|hahó}}, {{t|hu|figyelj}}, {{t|hu|figyu}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|hé}}, {{t|ga|hóigh}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|ehi}}, {{t|it|ou}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|おい|tr=oi}}, {{t+|ja|ねえ|tr=nē}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|ne}}, {{t|pam|na}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|이봐}}, {{t+|ko|어이}}, {{t+|ko|야}}\n* Latgalian: {{t|ltg|dzie}}, {{t|ltg|klaus}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|heus}}, {{t|la|eho}}, {{t+|la|salve}}, {{qualifier|to multiple people}} {{t+|la|salvete}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|klau}}, {{t+|lv|eu}}\n* Louisiana Creole: {{t|lou|hé}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|hei}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|ētē}}, {{t|mi|hā}}\n* Mongolian: {{t+|mn|хөөе}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|èp}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|هی|tr=hey}}, {{t+|fa|هلا|tr=halâ}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|hej}}, {{t+|pl|ej}}, {{t+|pl|e}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|ei}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|hei}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|эй}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|hòigh}}, {{t|gd|haoidh}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|хеј}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|hej}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|''imperative'' [[oír]]}}, {{t+|es|hey}}, {{t+|es|ey}}, {{t+|es|eh}}, {{t+|es|hao}} {{qualifier|especially at a distance}}, {{t|es|oe}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|du}}, {{t+|sv|hallå}}, {{t+|sv|öh}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|hoy}}, {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t|tl|huy}}, {{t+|tl|oi}}, {{t|tl|ui}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|гей}}, {{t|uk|ей}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|ê}}, {{t+|vi|này}}, {{t+|vi|ơi}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|protest or reprimand}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|հեյ}}, {{t+|hy|էյ}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ep}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hallo}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hé}}, {{t+|nl|hela}}, {{t+|nl|ho}}, {{t+|nl|hola}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|hei}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|hei}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|hé}}\n* German: {{t+|de|ey}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|állj}}, {{t+|hu|ácsi}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|ehi}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|おい|tr=oi}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|na}}, {{t|pam|ot}}, {{t|pam|oi}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|ej}}, {{t|pl|ejże}}, {{t+|pl|hola}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|ei}}, {{t|pt|epa}}, {{t+|pt|opa}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|эй}}, {{t+|ru|э}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|''imperative'' [[oír]]}}, {{t+|es|hey}}, {{t+|es|ey}}, {{t+|es|eh}}, {{t|es|oe}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hallå}}, {{t+|sv|du}}, {{t+|sv|öh}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|hoy}}, {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t|tl|huy}}, {{t+|tl|oi}}, {{t|tl|ui}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|ê}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|expression of surprise}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hè}}, {{t+|nl|huh}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|ohoh}}, {{t+|et|ohoo}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|oh-hoh}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|holà}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|nocsak}}, {{t+|hu|nahát}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|オラ|tr=ora}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|o}}, {{t+|pl|ojej}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|epa}}, {{t+|pt|opa}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|hop}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|ой}}, {{t+|ru|ух ты}}, {{t+|ru|ого́}}, {{t+|ru|ого́|tr=ohó}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|hey}}, {{t+|es|ey}}, {{t+|es|eh}}, {{t+|es|''imperative'' [[oír]]}}, {{t|es|oe}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|oj}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t+|tl|oi}}, {{t|tl|ui}}, {{t|tl|talaga}}, {{t+|tl|a}}, {{t|tl|ah}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|informal greeting}}\n* Alutor: {{t|alr|tr=mej}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|هَلَا}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|հեյ}}, {{t+|hy|ողջույն}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|ei}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ei}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|嗨}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hej}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hoi}}, {{t+|nl|hé}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|hej}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|hei}}, {{t+|fi|terve}}, {{t+|fi|moro}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|coucou}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hahó}}, {{t+|hu|helló}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|hóigh}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|ヘイ|tr=hei}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|na|}}, {{t|pam|oi}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|eho}}\n* Louisiana Creole: {{t|lou|hé}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|hej}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|oi}}, {{t+|pt|e aí}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|о}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}, {{t+|ru|ку-ку}} {{qualifier|familiar}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|hòigh}}, {{t|gd|shin thu}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|hey}}, {{t+|es|ey}}, {{t+|es|eh}}, {{t+|es|hola}}, {{t+|es|hopa}} {{qualifier|Colombia}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hej}}, {{t+|sv|hejsan}}, {{t+|sv|tjena}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|hoy}}, {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t|tl|huy}}, {{t+|tl|oi}}, {{t|tl|ui}}, {{t|tl|ei}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|request for repetition or explanation}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|eh}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|hei}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|micsoda}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|na}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|hã}}, {{t+|pt|hem}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|что}}, {{t+|ru|чо}} {{qualifier|colloquial, close to vulgar}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|hey}}, {{t+|es|ey}}, {{t+|es|eh}}, {{t+|es|''imperative'' [[oír]]}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hallå}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|huy}}, {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t|tl|ui}}, {{t|tl|ei}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|meaningless beat marker, filler syllable}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|hei}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|o}}, {{t+|la|ō}}, {{t|la|jo}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|é}}, {{t+|pt|hey}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hej}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|hoy}}, {{t|tl|uy}}, {{t|tl|ui}}, {{t|tl|oy}}, {{t|tl|huy}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* French: {{t+check|fr|hé}}, {{t+check|fr|eh}}, {{t+check|fr|hep}}\n* Slovene: {{t-check|sl|hej}}, {{t-check|sl|ej}}\n* Swedish: {{qualifier|1, 2, 3, 4, 5}} {{t+check|sv|hallå}}, {{qualifier|4}} {{t+check|sv|tja}}, {{qualifier|4, 6}} {{t+check|sv|hej}}, {{qualifier|6}} {{t-check|sv|hej hå}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|en|huh}}\n* {{l|en|hay is for horses}}\n* {{pedia}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# To greet with a \"hey\"\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{der|en|fr|haie||hedge}}, with reference to the weaving patterns used in hedgelaying. {{dbt|en|hedge|quay}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|dance}}{{lb|en|country dancing}} A [[choreographic]] [[figure]] in which three or more dancers [[weave]] between one another, passing by left and right shoulder alternately.\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|country dancing figure}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hej}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hey}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nSee ''[[he#Etymology 2|he]]''.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{alternative spelling of|en|he||Hebrew letter}}.\n\n====See also====\n* [[Yah-ta-hey]] {{i|etymologically unrelated}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ehy|Yeh|hye|yeh}}\n\n{{cln|en|greetings}}\n\n==Faroese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|fo}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|fo|[hɛi]}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|fo|interjection}}\n\n# [[hi]], {{l|en|hey}}, [[hello]]\n#: {{syn|fo|halló|góðan morgun|góðan dag|gott kvøld}}\n#: {{ant|fo|farvæl|vit síggjast}}\n#: {{ux|fo|'''hey''' aftur!|inline=1|hello again!}}\n\n{{cln|fo|phrasebook|greetings}}\n\n==Icelandic==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|is|non|hey}}, from {{inh|is|gem-pro|*hawją}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|is|/heiː/}}\n* {{rhymes|is|eiː|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{is-noun|@@}}\n\n# {{lb|is|usually|uncountable}} [[hay]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{is-ndecl|n.j}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|hīġ}}, {{m|ang|hīeġ}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*hawi}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*hawją||hay}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun|-}}\n\n# [[hay]]\n\n=====Alternative forms=====\n* {{alter|enm|heyȝ|heygh|hay|ay|heyn|hayn|hei|heiȝ|heigh|hai|hain}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|hay}}\n* {{desc|sco|hey}}\n* {{desc|yol|hye}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|hei|n|MED20239}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|*hē}}, {{m|ang|ēa}}. See English {{l|en|hey}} for more.\n\n====Interjection====\n{{head|enm|interjection}}\n\n# [[#English|hey]]\n\n=====Alternative forms=====\n* {{alter|enm|hay|ay|he|heh|heigh}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|hey}}\n* {{desc|sco|hey}}\n* {{desc|yol|ha}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|hei|interj|MED20240}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|heye||hedge}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|hye||haste}}\n\n===Etymology 5===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|he|t=he|id=he}}\n\n===Etymology 6===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|he|t=they|id=they}}\n\n===Etymology 7===\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|enm|verb|altform=1}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|heien||to lift up}}\n\n===Etymology 8===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|adjective|altform=1}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|heigh||high}}\n\n{{c|enm|Agriculture|Grasses}}\n{{cln|enm|greetings}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|pt|verb form}}\n\n# {{obsolete spelling of|pt|hei}}\n\n==Somali==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|so|verb}}\n\n# [[possess]]\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|es|ey}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|hey}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+|jei<q:imitating English>}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|es|interjection|head=¡hey!}}\n\n# {{l|en|hey}}!\n#: {{syn|es|eh|oye<l:tú>|oe|oí<l:vos>|oíd<l:vosotros>|hao<l:archaic>}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|es|ah|oh|hala}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{cln|es|greetings}}\n\n==Yola==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|yol|enm|heye}}, a conflation of {{inh|yol|ang|heġe|t=hedge, fence}} and {{inh|yol|ang|ġehæġ|t=an enclosed piece of land}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|yol|hye}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|yol|/heː/|/hai̯/}}\n* {{IPA|yol|/həi̯/<ref:{{R:Muirithe 1990|page=158}}>}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|yol|noun}}\n\n# [[garden]], [[field]], [[enclosure]]<ref>{{R:Poole 1867|page=45}}</ref>\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|page=46|title=GLOSSARY OF THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Chourch '''hey''';|translation=Church '''yard''';}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|yol|barach-hye}}\n* {{l|yol|chourch-hey}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|yol|noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|yol|hea||he}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>"}}